## Quick Start Commands

When user says "start services", "start dev", or "start all":

1. Start Docker databases first:
   ```bash
   docker-compose -f alpine-backend/docker-compose.local.yml up -d
   ```

2. Open 3 labeled split terminals and run:

   **Terminal 1 - "üöÄ Argo (8000)":**
   ```bash
   cd argo && source venv/bin/activate && uvicorn main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
   ```

   **Terminal 2 - "üîß Backend (9001)":**
   ```bash
   cd alpine-backend && source venv/bin/activate && uvicorn backend.main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 9001
   ```

   **Terminal 3 - "üåê Frontend (3001)":**
   ```bash
   cd alpine-frontend && pnpm dev
   ```

